  "source": "Corollary: \"Corollary 3.20\"\nof: \"Lemma 3.7 and the trichotomy law\"\ngiven: n, m is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nwhere: n != m\nthen:\n. have: n \\:proper.subset?:/ m\n  iff: n \"in\" m\nDocumented:\n. description: \"For all $n, m \\in \\omega$ with $n \\neq m$, $n \\in m$ if and only if $n \\subsetneq m$. This ties membership among natural numbers to proper containment.\"\nId: \"68bcb5f8-d1d4-4e0b-ab0b-3b3c3d4e8d4d\"",
